## Accounting Rules (NON-NEGOTIABLE)
```
NO ERP MODULE IS ALLOWED TO WRITE TO LEDGER TABLES DIRECTLY.
ALL FINANCIAL POSTINGS MUST PASS THROUGH THE ACCOUNTING POSTING ENGINE.
NO EXCEPTIONS.
```
See `.cursor/rules/accounting-posting-engine.mdc`

## Do NOT (Phase 6.A design phase)
- Build journal entry screens, voucher UI, or COA CRUD before implementation sprint
- Write to `accounting_*` ledger tables from Sales/Inventory/Purchase/etc.
- Skip Posting Engine for any financial transaction

